Music sensations Teni Makanaki and Abass Obesere are two of the leading music stars that thrilled guests at the Glo-sponsored Ojude Oba music show. Teni and Obesere led other music acts that performed at the music show which drew the curtain on the 2022 Ojude Oba festival sponsored by the digital solutions provider. The Ojude Oba Music Fiesta was held at the Equity Resort along  Erunwon Road,  Ijebu Ode, and also had Bash entertaining guests with humorous jokes.   Shoot Your Shot: Chef Sommy cooks up date to win crush’s…     I married who I wasn’t supposed to marry, says Kas Beats     Why I’m different from other musicians, says Berri-Tiga   It was also gathered that Globacom held a beauty pageant for solely Ijebu-born ladies to compete for the “Miss Ojude Oba” crown. Another highlight of the festival was the age grade contest, ‘Regberegbe,’ which saw the best-dressed age grade in the male and female categories winning N500,000, while the first and second runners-up went home with N300, 000 and N200,000 each. Globacom also rewarded the town’s different horse-riding families who showed mastery and exceptional skills on their horses with N300,000 for the winner and N200,000 and N100,000 for the first and second runners-up respectively.